==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|steop-|stēop-|deprived of a relative, step-|lang=ang}}, from {{proto|Germanic|steupa-|orphaned, step-|lang=en}}, from {{proto|Indo-European|(s)teup-|to push, strike|lang=en}}. Cognate with Dutch and German {{term|stief-||step-|lang=nl|lang=de}}, Icelandic {{term|stjúp-||step-|lang=is}}, Swedish {{term|styv-||step-|lang=sv}}. Related to Old English {{term|stiepan|stīepan|to deprive, bereave|lang=ang}}.

===Prefix===
{{en-prefix}}

# A prefix used before ''father'', ''mother'', ''brother'', ''sister'', ''son'', ''daughter'', ''child'', and so forth, to indicate that the person being identified is not a [[blood relative]] but is related through the [[marriage]] of a parent.

